<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-07-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="206" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                    <head>No. 206.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Maney</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-07-25"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 25,
                            1881</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 3.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I forward herewith, for your information, a
                        copy of my instruction<note n="*" xml:id="d206fn1">For inclosure see under
                            Great Britain.</note> to Mr. James R. Lowell, United States minister at
                        London, of the 24th ultimo, relative to an interoceanic canal across the
                        Isthmus of Panama.</p>
                    <p>A similar instruction was also addressed to the representatives of this
                        government accredited to the seveal European Governments.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>JAMES G. BLAINE.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>